HEADWORD: Foreknow
<hw>Fore*know"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Foreknew</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Foreknown</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Foreknowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To have previous
knowledge of; to know beforehand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who would the miseries of man <qex>foreknow</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreknowable</ent>⟦br⟧
